fix:
private boolean hasExceptionHandler(AstNode node) {
  while (node != null) {
    if (node instanceof BlockTryStatement || AstVisitor.hasProperty(node.getClass(), PROPERTY_CATCH)) {
      return true;
    }
    node = node.parent;
  }
  return false;
}

issue_description:
What steps will reproduce the problem?

Starting with this code:

-----
function a() {
 var x = '1';
 try {
  x += somefunction();
 } catch(e) {
 }
 x += "2";
 try {
  x += somefunction();
 } catch(e) {
 }
 document.write(x);
}

a();
a();
-----

It gets compiled to:

-----
function b() {
  var a;
  try {
    a = "1" + somefunction()
  }catch(c) {
  }
  try {
    a = a + "2" + somefunction()
  }catch(d) {
  }
  document.write(a)
}
b();
b();
-----

What is the expected output? What do you see instead?

The problem is that it's including the constant "1" and "2" inside the try block when the shouldn't be. When executed uncompiled, the script prints "1212". When compiled, the script prints "undefinedundefined".

This behavior doesn't happen if the entire function gets inlined, or if the code between the two try blocks is sufficiently complex.

